OL,3,CEnergy price cap predicted to rise in
OL,4,CJanuary, raising household bills by 1%
OL,6,FITV News' business editor Joel Hills
OL,7,Fexplains why energy costs are rising
OL,9,FEnergy bills could be set to increase
OL,10,Fby 1% in the new year, as analysts
OL,11,Fhave forecasted a price cap rise in
OL,12,FJanuary.
OL,14,FEnergy consultancy Cornwall Insight
OL,15,Fsaid it expects Ofgem to announce a
OL,16,Fhike in the typical household's energy
OL,17,Fbill by #19, up to #1,736 from #1,717
OL,18,Fon January 1.
