OL,3,CEnergy price cap predicted to rise in
OL,4,CJanuary, raising household bills by 1%
OL,6,FThe consultancy had previously
OL,7,Fpredicted a 1% fall, but said this was
OL,8,Fnow no longer the case. The predicted
OL,9,Fhike comes after energy prices rose by
OL,10,F10% in October.
OL,12,FCornwall Insight said: "Given the
OL,13,Fprice cap rise in October, many will
OL,14,Fhave been hoping to see a fall in the
OL,15,Fcap for January. Unfortunately,
OL,16,Fforecasts show that prices will be
OL,17,Fstaying relatively high for the
OL,18,Fremainder of winter."
