OL,3,CEnergy price cap predicted to rise in
OL,4,CJanuary, raising household bills by 1%
OL,6,FDespite January's forecast increase,
OL,7,Fprices are still expected to fall
OL,8,Fslightly in both the second and fourth
OL,9,Fquarters of next year.
OL,11,FOfgem changes the price cap for
OL,12,Fhouseholds every three months, largely
OL,13,Fbased on the cost of energy on
OL,14,Fwholesale markets. The regulator will
OL,15,Fconfirm the level for the first
OL,16,Fquarter of next year on November 22.
